el. The book provides case studies of DLBE teachers who: (a) implemented the DLBE model with fidelity; (b) struggled to implement the DLBE model; and (c) adapted the DLBE model to meet the needs of their local classroom context. The book demonstrates the way teachers as language policymakers navigate and interpret district-wide DLBE implementation and the tensions that surface through this process. The research, conducted over four years using a variety of methods, highlights the challenges and opportunities faced by teachers implementing DLBE, and will be of interest to both teachers and administrators of DLBE programs as well as scholars working in bilingual education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation, BilingualvCase studies. 0aEducation, BilingualxStudy and teaching. 0aEducation, Bilingual-Case studies. 0aSecond language acquisitionvCase studies. 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teaching. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDBLE.  aDual Language and Dual Immersion.  aEducation of emerging bilingual students.  aTeachers as language policymakers.  abilingual education.  adual language bilingual education.  adual language programs.  adual language teaching.  aforeign language immersion.  aheritage language programs.  alanguage policy.  aone-way dual language.  ateacher cases.  atwo-way dual language.1 aPalmer, Deborah K., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKA